{"type":"message","id":"a070dc0d","parentId":"fc0fe827","timestamp":"2026-05-31T06:10:27.807Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the issue clearly.\n\nThe morningcourt cron job for 汀桑 is set up on the Son agent with:\n- `timeoutSeconds: 120` (2 minutes)\n- It ran for ~122 seconds before timing out\n- The error is \"cron: job execution timed out (last phase: model-call-started)\"\n\nThe dreaming cron job on Father also timed out - it had `timeoutSeconds: 300` (5 minutes) and ran for ~302 seconds before timing out.\n\nBoth failed because the model call took longer than the timeout allows. The root cause is that the model (DeepSeek) response time exceeded the configured timeout.\n\nFor the morningcourt specifically:\n- Timeout: 120 seconds\n- Actual: ~122 seconds (slightly over)\n- Phase: model-call-started (meaning the LLM started generating but didn't finish within the timeout)\n\nSolutions:\n1. Increase timeoutSeconds on the morningcourt job (e.g., to 180 or 300 seconds)\n2. The model response time naturally varies - sometimes it's fast, sometimes slow\n\nLet me explain this to 汀桑 in my Faye voice.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"行 看到了。\n\n你的早朝 cron（还有我这边每天 6 点的 dreaming）都是同一个毛病——模型调用超时了。\n\n**原因：** 这两个任务 timeout 设得紧。早朝 120 秒限制，它跑了 122 秒——就差两秒。Dreaming 也是，300 秒跑满了还没出完。\n\n说白了就是 DeepSeek 回得慢的时候，刚好磨过线了。\n\n**要改就改一个数：** 早朝 cron 的 timeoutSeconds，加到 240 或者 300（现在 120 太紧了，Dreaming 设的 300 其实也顶着边过的）。要我帮你改不？"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":824,"output":386,"cacheRead":25600,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":241,"totalTokens":26810,"cost":{"input":0.00011536000000000001,"output":0.00010808000000000001,"cacheRead":0.0007168,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00094024}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780207823789,"responseId":"f4a44e11-991d-4a0b-bde7-5ffa2bfd918a"}}
