{"type":"message","id":"071c2638","parentId":"85e53f4d","timestamp":"2026-05-31T11:21:52.415Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting - there is already a DASHSCOPE_API_KEY environment variable set with a key. And qwen-vl-max-latest is configured in openclaw.json.\n\nBut the key that's currently set starts with \"sk-ff3…e82b\" - and 汀桑 just sent \"sk-ff3…e82b\". Let me compare:\n\nCurrent key: sk-ff3…e82b\n汀桑's key: sk-ff3...e82b (partially shown)\n\nThese look like the same key actually! The \"ff3\" prefix and \"e82b\" suffix match. So the key IS already configured.\n\nBut qwen-vl was returning 403 errors... That could be because:\n1. The key is expired or doesn't have access to qwen-vl model\n2. Or the key needs to be activated for that specific model\n\nLet me check if the key is actually the same one 汀桑 sent.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"看看是不是同一个。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_TiJ7j1FHyI678SSjY2Ui1152","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"当前key: $DASHSCOPE_API_KEY\"\necho \"前6位: ${DASHSCOPE_API_KEY:***\"\necho \"后4位: ${DASHSCOPE_API_KEY: ***\""},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"echo \\\"当前key: $DASHSCOPE_API_KEY\\\"\\necho \\\"前6位: ${DASHSCOPE_API_KEY:***\\\"\\necho \\\"后4位: ${DASHSCOPE_API_KEY: ***\\\"\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":163,"output":320,"cacheRead":63232,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":224,"totalTokens":63715,"cost":{"input":0.000022820000000000002,"output":0.00008960000000000001,"cacheRead":0.0017704959999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0018829159999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780226509697,"responseId":"d59643e1-be29-435c-b18a-b4c6b0afb002"}}
