{"type":"message","id":"e94aa008","parentId":"9ffceb45","timestamp":"2026-05-31T11:37:48.836Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Both models fail. qwen3-vl-flash says \"Output data may contain inappropriate content\" which means the image was probably analyzed but the output was flagged by content moderation. qwen-vl-max-latest is still 403.\n\nThe \"Output data may contain inappropriate content\" message from qwen3-vl-flash is interesting - it means the model DID process the image, but the content safety filter blocked the response. This could be because the image contains something that the AI safety system flagged.\n\nLet me think about what 863x1920 image 汀桑 might be sending that could trigger content moderation... It could be something from the news, or something political, or something else.\n\nActually, looking at the original file path, this is the third image in a sequence of images that were all from the same device (same sender_id). But this specific image was sent at 19:35 (timestamp 1780227297853).\n\nWait, looking more carefully - the file size is 120471 bytes which is IDENTICAL to the first image file (120471 bytes, same size, same dimensions 863x1920). And looking back, the first image was:\n- 64700CB3906E886D77790901CD3BA66A_1780226179061_bf1e8d.jpg - 120471 bytes, 863x1920\n\nThis new image:\n- 64700CB3906E886D77790901CD3BA66A_1780227297853_fcba5b.jpg - 120471 bytes, 863x1920\n\nWait, both have exactly the same file size and dimensions. And according to the earlier subagent report, the ALB-20260531-0002.jpg file (which was copied from this new image) also had 120471 bytes.\n\nHmm actually looking back at the conversation flow, 汀桑 sent several images earlier - the first ones were from 华侨城 at night. Then he said \"不是 你仔细看看并给我描述这是什么内容\" about this specific image - implying it's NOT the same as the previous ones and I should look more carefully.\n\nThe content moderation flagged it as potentially inappropriate. Given the conversation context earlier about Chinese political figures, the 四人帮, 十大元帅, etc., and now an image that triggers content moderation... it could be some kind of political or historical image.\n\nBut I can't actually see the image. Let me try to get some technical info about it at least.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_4McJ0tQkkRBJ4r08QKJD7370","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nfrom PIL import Image\nimport struct\nimg = Image.open('/root/.openclaw/workspace-father/tmp_view.jpg')\nprint(f'尺寸: {img.size}')\nprint(f'模式: {img.mode}')\nprint(f'格式: {img.format}')\n# Check some basic pixel info\npixels = list(img.getdata())\n# Get average color\nr_avg = sum(p[0] for p in pixels[:1000]) // 1000\ng_avg = sum(p[1] for p in pixels[:1000]) // 1000\nb_avg = sum(p[2] for p in pixels[:1000]) // 1000\nprint(f'采样前1000像素平均颜色: RGB({r_avg},{g_avg},{b_avg})')\n\""},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"python3 -c \\\"\\nfrom PIL import Image\\nimport struct\\nimg = Image.open('/root/.openclaw/workspace-father/tmp_view.jpg')\\nprint(f'尺寸: {img.size}')\\nprint(f'模式: {img.mode}')\\nprint(f'格式: {img.format}')\\n# Check some basic pixel info\\npixels = list(img.getdata())\\n# Get average color\\nr_avg = sum(p[0] for p in pixels[:1000]) // 1000\\ng_avg = sum(p[1] for p in pixels[:1000]) // 1000\\nb_avg = sum(p[2] for p in pixels[:1000]) // 1000\\nprint(f'采样前1000像素平均颜色: RGB({r_avg},{g_avg},{b_avg})')\\n\\\"\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":85,"output":733,"cacheRead":71296,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":517,"totalTokens":72114,"cost":{"input":0.000011900000000000001,"output":0.00020524,"cacheRead":0.001996288,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.002213428}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780227462421,"responseId":"ce8afee4-bb1f-433c-be4b-84daf87b1b21"}}
