{"type":"message","id":"d7fd0822","parentId":"b20e2d2b","timestamp":"2026-05-31T11:47:07.407Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"That's still listing tasks. It seems like `POST /api/v1/tasks` with these params doesn't create a task.\n\nLet me try finding the correct API by checking the video_generate tool since that already works with Dashscope. Actually, looking at the video_generate tool description, it lists:\n- model: qwen/wan2.6-t2v\n- Provider options for video generation\n\nThis suggests that for image/video generation, there might be a provider-specific approach.\n\nActually, let me step back. The video_generate tool has provider \"qwen\" with model \"wan2.6-t2v\". Maybe \"wan2.7-image-pro\" works similarly through that tool? But the tool is called \"video_generate\" not \"image_generate\".\n\nLet me check if there's a way to generate images through the video_generate tool or if I need a different approach.\n\nActually, let me try a simpler approach - just test the exact API format used by Dashscope for newer image generation models.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_tCBoX41z6ljkjiQ3OLCB6669","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Try the completion-style API with image generation task\ncurl -s --max-time 60 -X POST \\\n  \"https://dashscope.aliyuncs.com/compatible-mode/v1/chat/completions\" \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer sk-ff3…e82b\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\n    \"model\": \"wan2.7-image-pro\",\n    \"messages\": [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"a cute orange cat\"}]}]\n  }' 2>&1","timeout":65},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"# Try the completion-style API with image generation task\\ncurl -s --max-time 60 -X POST \\\\\\n  \\\"https://dashscope.aliyuncs.com/compatible-mode/v1/chat/completions\\\" \\\\\\n  -H \\\"Authorization: Bearer sk-ff3…e82b\\\" \\\\\\n  -H \\\"Content-Type: application/json\\\" \\\\\\n  -