{"type":"message","id":"9ff207cf","parentId":"54f107fa","timestamp":"2026-05-31T12:18:12.326Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see the structure. I need to add a `minimax` provider before the closing `}` of the providers block, and then also add the API key to the auth section.\n\nThe providers block ends at around line 265. I'll add minimax after dashscope.\n\nFor MiniMax, the API is at `https://api.minimaxi.com` and uses a custom API format (not OpenAI-compatible). The music generation endpoint is `POST /v1/music_generation`.\n\nSince it's not an OpenAI-compatible API, I can't just add it as a model provider. I need to either:\n1. Use a different approach - store the key and let Son call the API directly via curl\n2. Add it as a provider with the right api format\n\nActually, looking at how the providers work, they all use \"openai-completions\" or \"anthropic-messages\" etc. as the api type. MiniMax's music API is a custom API.\n\nThe simplest approach is to just store the key as an environment variable and let Son's function use curl to call the MiniMax API directly - same pattern as the draw function that calls Wan2.7's async API.\n\nLet me save the key as an environment variable and update Son's function to use it.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"MiniMax 的 API 不是 OpenAI 兼容格式，不适合直接当 provider 配。我存成环境变量，让 Son 直接调。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_tIpohQ2XcxsaFaRsoJaT4237","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Save the key to environment\necho 'export MINIMAX_API_KEY=\"sk-api…xIA0\"' >> /root/.openclaw/workspace-son/.env\necho \"done\""},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"# Save the key to environment\\necho 'export MINIMAX_API_KEY=\\\"sk-api…xIA0\\\"' >> /root/.openclaw/workspace-son/.env\\necho \\\"done\\\"\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":387,"output":461,"cacheRead":123392,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":266,"totalT