{"type":"message","id":"a98e0593","parentId":"47e4a744","timestamp":"2026-05-31T12:56:11.283Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"\"invalid api key\" (status_code 2049) - this key is not valid at all. A completely different error from the previous ones. The key format might be wrong - maybe it's a MiniMax \"group key\" not an API key, or the key was copied incorrectly.\n\nWait, let me look at the key more carefully. The test I just ran used the full key string. Let me check if the env file has it correctly and if the curl command used it correctly.\n\nActually, looking at the output, I see the curl command used the key inline: `\"Authorization: Bearer sk-cp-…0Y98\"` which looks correct.\n\nBut status 2049 \"invalid api key\" means the key itself is not recognized. Maybe:\n1. The key was copied incorrectly (汀桑 might have copied something extra)\n2. The key hasn't been activated yet\n3. It's the wrong type of key\n\nLet me check the key length.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_YSVgBT4B6IMWuBsGrRbS7043","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"source /root/.openclaw/workspace-son/.env\necho \"Length: ${#MINIMAX_API_KEY}\"\necho \"Starts: ${MINIMAX_API_KEY:***\"\necho \"Ends: ${MINIMAX_API_KEY: ***\""},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"source /root/.openclaw/workspace-son/.env\\necho \\\"Length: ${#MINIMAX_API_KEY}\\\"\\necho \\\"Starts: ${MINIMAX_API_KEY:***\\\"\\necho \\\"Ends: ${MINIMAX_API_KEY: ***\\\"\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":66,"output":376,"cacheRead":150272,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":279,"totalTokens":150714,"cost":{"input":0.000009240000000000001,"output":0.00010528000000000001,"cacheRead":0.004207616,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.004322136}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780232166016,"responseId":"a8ec23d7-ae50-4570-8e3c-b8b26c25fb46"}}
