{"type":"message","id":"faa5d09e","parentId":"1303312b","timestamp":"2026-05-31T12:56:19.042Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The key looks correct in the env file. But the test returned \"2049 invalid api key\". \n\nThe previous key also weirdly had 125 chars... Let me check if maybe this is a group API key and not a regular API key. MiniMax has different types of keys - group keys vs personal keys. Group keys might need a different prefix or different auth format.\n\nActually, let me look at the MiniMax error code:\n- 2049: 无效的api key\n\nThe key starts with `sk-cp-` which is different from the previous key which also started with `sk-cp-Xr...`. But the previous key returned \"login fail: Please carry the API secret key in the 'Authorization' field\" (1004) instead of \"invalid api key\" (2049).\n\nThis new key is actually recognized differently - it's returning a different status code. Status 2049 means \"invalid api key\" - the key format is not recognized at all.\n\nMaybe 汀桑's new key needs to be activated first on the MiniMax platform, or maybe he needs to make sure it's copied exactly right. Let me tell him.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"`status_code: 2049` — 无效的 API key。新生成的这个 key MiniMax 那边不认。\n\n你看看在 `platform.minimaxi.com` → 接口密钥 那里：\n1. 这个 key 是不是**复制完整了**？有没有多复制空格或者漏了字符？\n2. 还是说要先在控制台里点一下**启用/激活**才能用？"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":205,"output":321,"cacheRead":150784,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":237,"totalTokens":151310,"cost":{"input":0.000028700000000000003,"output":0.00008988,"cacheRead":0.004221952,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.004340532}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780232174924,"responseId":"7059f6b3-7ea8-41e1-9eab-b0db2b6e00b1"}}
