{"type":"message","id":"e0325c0c","parentId":"fa69306f","timestamp":"2026-05-31T14:10:19.389Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me try a different approach. I can use the `qqbot_channel_api` tool to send a file message to the user. The QQ Bot API for sending C2C (私聊) messages has a media endpoint.\n\nActually, looking at the QQ Bot API docs, to send a file in a C2C message:\n1. First upload the file to get a `file_uuid`\n2. Then send a message referencing that file_uuid\n\nBut I don't have a specific tool for file uploading. Let me try a simpler approach.\n\nActually, maybe I should just check what qqbot_channel_api tool can do. Let me try to use it.\n\nWait, I don't have a `qqbot_channel_api` tool available in my tool list. The skill says I should use it but it's not listed in my available tools. So I can't use it.\n\nLet me think about another approach. The `<qqmedia>` tag is how OpenClaw sends media. Since .mp3 is routed as voice, maybe I can try a different format.\n\nActually, the simplest solution is to just rename the file to something that falls through to \"文件\" category. `.music` extension is not in any of the recognized lists, so it would be sent as a file.\n\nLet me try that.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"QQ Bot 对 mp3 固定走语音通道。我换个不受影响的扩展名发你，你收到后改回 `.mp3` 就行。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_gHSuSvucie71ZLqy7VtO6851","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cp /root/.openclaw/media/qqbot/compose_test.mp3 /root/.openclaw/media/qqbot/compose_test.music"},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"cp /root/.openclaw/media/qqbot/compose_test.mp3 /root/.openclaw/media/qqbot/compose_test.music\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":143,"output":375,"cacheRead":175488,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":270,"totalTokens":176006,"cost":{"input":0.00002002,"output":0.000105,"cacheRead":0.004913664,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.005038684}},"stopReaso