{"type":"message","id":"c37a151a","parentId":"723e7ce2","timestamp":"2026-05-31T14:12:47.211Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"QQ Bot doesn't support calling the API directly like this for C2C file uploads through these endpoints. \n\nLet me think about another approach. OpenClaw's `<qqmedia>` tag is the native way. Since `.mp3` gets routed as voice, and changing the extension makes it unrecognizable...\n\nActually, maybe I should just accept the limitation. The `<qqmedia>` tag sends mp3 as voice messages on QQ Bot. There's no way around it through the OpenClaw framework without modifying the underlying handler.\n\nOr wait - what if I pack it as a zip file? `.zip` is not in any media category → goes as \"文件\". The user can extract and play.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"QQ Bot 的 C2C 文件接口走不通。那我换个法子——打包成 zip 发你，你收到解压就是 mp3。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_YxcRbqj8cxlaPGiAtbBh5128","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/media/qqbot && zip -j compose_test.zip compose_test.mp3 && ls -lh compose_test.zip"},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"cd /root/.openclaw/media/qqbot && zip -j compose_test.zip compose_test.mp3 && ls -lh compose_test.zip\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":142,"output":244,"cacheRead":179072,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":142,"totalTokens":179458,"cost":{"input":0.000019880000000000003,"output":0.00006832000000000001,"cacheRead":0.005014016,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.005102216}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780236763515,"responseId":"560e472c-a479-4d4b-afc2-4ccf2fe0a50c"}}
